<p>I have a code block say</p>  <pre><code>if(xxxx) { //do something for xxx } else if(yyyy) {     //do something for yyyy } </code></pre>  <p>and want to add it for many cases(~50). I don't want to type in</p>  <pre><code>    if(xxxx)     {        //do something for xxx     } </code></pre>  <p>everytime.</p>  <p>Can I add a shortcut like , pressing xx + SPACE would replace 'xx' with  </p>  <pre><code>if(xxxx)         {            //do something for xxx         } </code></pre>  <p>and pressing 'yy + SPACE' would replace 'yy' with </p>  <pre><code>else if(yyyy)     {         //do something for yyyy     } </code></pre>  <p>The code segments 'xxxx' represent expressions and I need to alter them for certain scenarios, so not looking for <em>Find and Replace</em> (or using Regex for that matter). Something on the lines of <code>sout</code> to <code>System.out.println()</code></p>